The paper focuses on video understanding, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new deep neural network architecture for multi-label and multi-task learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The dataset and taxonomy presented in the paper also involve semantic aspects, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of spatio-temporal features, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
